# Figma

## MCP setup

**Claude Code:** The Figma MCP server is connected at session start via the MCP config. See `docs/FIGMA_SETUP.md` for full setup.

**Cursor:** Use `/add-plugin figma` in agent chat to connect the Figma MCP server.

## Project-specific rules

- **Map to our system** — Treat Figma MCP output as design reference, not final code. Use this project's design tokens (`tailwind.config.ts`), components (`components/`), and typography (Fraunces headings, Inter body). Validate for 1:1 visual parity with the Figma screenshot.
- **Reuse, don't duplicate** — Use existing design-system components. Do not add new icon packages if assets come from Figma. No hardcoded colors or spacing; use tokens from `tailwind.config.ts`.
- **Asset handling** — If the Figma MCP server returns a `localhost` source for an image or SVG, use that source directly. Do not create placeholders.

## OpenSpec `design.md`

For changes under `openspec/changes/<id>/`, every **`design.md` MUST include a “Visual design / Figma” subsection** (use “N/A” table rows for API-only work). For UI work, specify:

- Primary **Figma file URL** (`figma.com/design/...` or board URL)
- **Published libraries** used (team kit, community DS, or hub library)
- **Frames/components in scope**
- Whether **Code Connect** mappings need updates (`figma-code-connect` skill)

### File page/frame naming convention (REQUIRED)

Every OpenSpec Figma file uses **numbered pages** and treats each proposal iteration as a distinct page — never edit or append to an existing proposal page in place:

- `00 Components` — imported DS components + local "hub tokens" variable collection.
- `01 Current state` — the as-is frame(s), reconstructed from code or captured from the running app.
- `02 Proposed` — the first proposed iteration.
- `02.1`, `02.2`, … — **each subsequent proposal iteration is a NEW numbered page** (`02.1 Proposed — <what changed>`), so prior iterations stay intact for comparison. **Never** overwrite or append frames on an already-built/approved proposal page.
- Name frames within a page by treatment + breakpoint, e.g. `Proposed · Desktop 1024`, `Proposed · Mobile 480`.

Record the exact page names + frame node IDs in the `design.md` Visual design table, and restate this file convention there (as `stop-the-leaks/design.md` does).

Map kit variables to **`tailwind.config.ts`** tokens; treat MCP-exported layout as reference, not literals (see Project-specific rules above).

## Component annotation

See `component-conventions.mdc` for the `@figma` JSDoc comment format used to link React components to their Figma counterparts, and for the hub design file key.

## Skills

Seven Figma workflow skills are fetched from `github.com/figma/mcp-server-guide` at session start and available via `/skill-name`:

- `/figma-use` — execute JavaScript via the Figma Plugin API (required before all write operations)
- `/figma-implement-design` — translate a Figma URL into code using project tokens and components
- `/figma-generate-design` — build full screens in Figma using the design system
- `/figma-generate-library` — generate a complete design system in Figma from the codebase
- `/figma-code-connect` — map Figma components to code implementations (Org/Enterprise only)
- `/figma-create-design-system-rules` — generate project-level Figma rules for Claude/Cursor
- `/figma-create-new-file` — create a new Figma design or FigJam file
